claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table showing pre- and post-vaccination geometric mean antibody titers (with 95% CI) and percent response rates for three influenza vaccine antigens (A/Solomon Island/3/2006 H1N1, A/Wisconsin/67/2005 H3N2, B/Malaysia/2506/2004) across four groups (Placebo, FluBlok, FluBlok PV, FluBlok NPV). The table presents immunogenicity data (antibody titers and response rates) and does not include any information on hemagglutinin (HA) microgram content per strain for FluBlok or standard-dose vaccines, so it does not support the claim.
